  "body": "<!---\r\nThanks for creating a Pull Request 💖!\r\n\r\nPlease read the following before submitting:\r\n- PRs that add new external dependencies might take a while to review.\r\n- Keep your PR as small as possible.\r\n- Limit your PR to one type (docs, feature, refactoring, ci, or bugfix)\r\n-->\r\n\r\nCloses # <!-- Github issue # here -->\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\nCurrently, the avatar component has a fallback to generate initials with random and accessible background colours.\r\nBut If the users name more than 2 words, initials do not get displayed as expected.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behaviour (updates)\r\n\r\nIf the user name is `Anil Pak`, it's displayed as `AP`, but If the user name is `Anil Pak Chakra` it will be also displayed as `AP` instead of `AC`\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\nWith these changes instead of splitting the name as first_name and last_name, we are splitting the string name to the array and taking the first letter from the first and the last word to create initials.\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\nNot sure :)\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n",
